-- int_deduped_returns.sql
```sql
-- Intermediate layer: deduplicate multiple returns per item, keep one approved
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        return_id,
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY CASE WHEN status = 'approved' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END,
                     return_date DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- int_items_with_returns.sql
```sql
-- Intermediate layer: join items with deduped returns and products
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.order_id,
        oi.product_id,
        oi.quantity,
        p.category_id,
        CASE WHEN dr.item_id IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_returned
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
        ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} dr
        ON dr.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    order_id,
    product_id,
    quantity,
    category_id,
    is_returned
FROM source
```

-- Intermediate layer: enrich with category names, handle missing categories
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        iwc.item_id,
        iwc.quantity,
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name,
        iwc.is_returned
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_returns') }} iwc
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = iwc.category_id
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    quantity,
    category_name,
    is_returned
FROM source
```

-- fct_return_rates_by_category.sql
```sql
-- Mart layer: calculate return rates by category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        category_name,
        SUM(quantity) AS total_items_sold,
        SUM(quantity * is_returned) AS total_items_returned
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_category') }}
    GROUP BY category_name
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    total_items_sold,
    total_items_returned,
    ROUND(
        CAST(total_items_returned AS DECIMAL(10,2)) / CAST(total_items_sold AS DECIMAL(10,2)),
        4
    ) AS return_rate
FROM source
ORDER BY category_name ASC
